text: I was hired as a three-month contractor
to copy and paste things onto websites
at my company which suddenly made me
think maybe I should learn some coding
when I was around eight or nine my
family got dial-up internet for the
first time and I had a family member who
showed me how to go to ask geez calm and
if you typed a question in there stuff
would pop up in the screen and I asked
that family member wait where did that
come from how did it know what I was
trying to search for how does that work
and they said oh it's just programming
stuff and I never really thought much
about it later on but now that I get to
work as a full-stack developer and I
understand more about where that comes
from when I'm working with websites and
search engines it's just like oh my
goodness I used to wonder about this as
a kid and now I get to know how it works
if you come from a hard background or if
you didn't have the economical help to
complete school like maybe most other
people were able to do you should not
let that discourage you there's a lot of
other options out there I've had so many
people tell me no you can't do that
unless you have been able to do X Y & Z
so far in your life and I kind of like -
wrong
